"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.6.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.6.1</span> 標題：天平（balance scales）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מֹאזְנַיִם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： m’oznayim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:36\">LEV 19:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:2\">JOB 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:6\">JOB 31:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:10\">PSA 62:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:12\">ISA 40:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:15\">ISA 40:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:10\">JER 32:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:1\">EZK 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:10\">EZK 45:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:8\">HOS 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:11\">MIC 6:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Aramaic</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">蘭：מֹאזְנֵא</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： mo’zne’)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:27\">DAN 5:27</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： פֶּלֶס</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： peles)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:12\">ISA 40:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： קָנֶה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： qaneh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:6\">ISA 46:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ζυγός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： zugos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:5\">REV 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:25\">SIR 21:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:25\">SIR 28:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir42:4\">SIR 42:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： πλάστιγξ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： plastigx)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis11:22\">WIS 11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc9:8\">2MA 9:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ῥοπή</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： rhopē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir1:22\">SIR 1:22</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： σταθμός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： stathmion, stathmos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:15\">SIR 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir26:15\">SIR 26:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:25\">SIR 28:25</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Latin</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">拉： statera</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd3:34\">2ES 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd4:36\">2ES 4:36</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0351_balance_scales.jpg\" alt=\"天平秤\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">天平秤 (Gary Todd, Israel Museum, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>天平是稱量物體重量的工具。古代常見的天平是由一根木桿加上兩端的秤盤組成，木桿的中點繫著一根繩子或鏈子，把天平吊起來進行稱重。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>使用時，把法碼（或砝碼）放在天平一端的秤盤內，待稱重物品放在另一端的秤盤內。測量者把天平提起來，當木桿與地面平行時，表示兩個秤盤裡的東西重量相同。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在有些語言中，「天平」可以譯為「稱重工具」或「確定某物的重量所用的器具」。翻譯者應避免使用不符合時代的、表示各種現代秤的用詞，例如彈簧秤、液壓秤等。</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0016_balance_scales.png\" alt=\"使用天平秤的男人\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">使用天平秤的男人 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>許多考古遺址都曾發現不同時期的法碼（也有體積量器），這些法碼通常是球形的石頭，上面刻有重量標記。這些法碼的製作相對粗糙，從現代的標準來看，算不上「精確」或「公平」。但是，在特定的時間和地點，這些法碼仍可作為一種規範標準，儘管不同時間地點的標準各異。因此，用現代重量單位翻譯的對等詞僅僅是近似值。</p>\n<p>這種古代天平的工作原理是比較兩個物體的相對重量，因此在兩約之間的時期，天平成為一種象徵，意指考量兩種活動或兩種選擇的相對價值或對錯。比較英文慣用語“weigh his actions”（英文直譯：「稱一稱他的行為」）。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir1:22\">SIR 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:25\">SIR 21:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir28:25\">SIR 28:25</a> 出現了這種比喻用法；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:27\">DAN 5:27</a> 也有一定程度的喻義。很多時候，翻譯者可以不提到這種物品，而是按照喻義進行翻譯；例如，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:25\">SIR 21:25</a> 可作「聰明人會考慮他們的話語所帶來的結果」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。同樣，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir1:22\">SIR 1:22</a> 的原文字面意為「人的怒氣使天平向著他的毀滅傾斜」，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 採用了直譯，然而也可譯為「它（怒氣）會使你身敗名裂」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 英文直譯）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
